@startuml scenario_lock_to_manual_override_release_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Scenario Lock To Manual Override Release Signal Flow\n(Input_Console -> TEST_SCN / TEST_BAS -> Router compat)

actor "Operator\n(Scenario Tab)" as Operator #F4F7FB
participant "Input_Console\nScenario controls" as Panel #E8F0FE
participant "TEST_SCN\nscenario harness owner" as TEST_SCN #FFE6E6
participant "TEST_BAS\nbase lifecycle mirror" as TEST_BAS #FFF4CC
participant "INPUT_CONSOLE_ROUTER\nmanual compat publisher" as Router #E8F7E8
participant "Core / Inject\nmanual seams" as Manual #E8F0FE

== Scenario Start ==

Operator -> Panel : Click scenario preset
activate Panel
Panel -> TEST_SCN : Test::scenarioCommand\nor compat Test::testScenario
deactivate Panel

activate TEST_SCN
TEST_SCN -> TEST_SCN : applyScenarioPanelRequest()
TEST_SCN -> TEST_SCN : set scenarioCommandAck / activeId
note right of TEST_SCN
Scenario harness owns:
- scenario start/stop acceptance
- active scenario lifecycle
- scenario lock payload staging
end note
TEST_SCN -> TEST_BAS : Test::scenarioCommandAck\nTest::scenarioActiveId
deactivate TEST_SCN

== Scenario Lock Active ==

activate TEST_BAS
TEST_BAS -> TEST_BAS : stageBaseScenarioLifecycle()
TEST_BAS -> TEST_BAS : publishInputConsoleManualCompat()
note right of TEST_BAS
While active, manual panel mirrors
follow scenario lifecycle state rather
than free manual exploration intent.
end note
TEST_BAS -> Router : compat publish trigger
deactivate TEST_BAS

activate Router
Router -> Router : isScenarioLocked() == 1
Router -> Manual : compatPoliceDispatch /\ncompatAmbulanceDispatch /\ncompatEmergencyDirection /\ncompatEmergencyEta /\ncompatEmergencySourceId
deactivate Router

== Stop / Manual Release ==

Operator -> Panel : Click STOP / MANUAL
activate Panel
Panel -> TEST_SCN : Test::scenarioStopReq = 1
deactivate Panel

activate TEST_SCN
TEST_SCN -> TEST_SCN : applyScenarioPanelRequest(0, 1)
TEST_SCN -> TEST_SCN : clear scenarioActiveId /\ncommandAck / testScenario mirror
TEST_SCN -> TEST_BAS : scenarioActiveId = 0
deactivate TEST_SCN

activate TEST_BAS
TEST_BAS -> TEST_BAS : maybeClearBaseStateOnHarnessIdle()
TEST_BAS -> Router : publishInputConsoleManualCompat()
deactivate TEST_BAS

activate Router
Router -> Router : isScenarioLocked() == 0
Router -> Manual : manualAlertOverrideCmd /\nmanual emergency compat mirrors restored
note right of Router
Release effect
- scenario lock no longer dominates
- Input_Console manual overrides
  become the active manual source again
end note
deactivate Router

note over Operator, Manual
Representative runtime chain
1. Scenario preset starts TEST_SCN lifecycle
2. TEST_BAS mirrors lifecycle and publishes lock-aware compat state
3. Router exposes scenario-dominant manual mirrors while locked
4. STOP/MANUAL clears lifecycle
5. Router returns control to free manual override inputs
end note

@enduml
